NAME 
    write-to-history
     
DESCRIPTION
    Write input or file contents to bash/shell history
       ~ Requires 'HISTFILE' to be defined       

   When --file is specified, perform a cat of the file contents to the history file. 
   Otherwise, read standard input and echo the input to the history file.

   With no INPUT or FILE specified, user is prompted to input value using standard read input.

SYNOPSIS
     write-to-history [INPUT]
     write-to-history [OPTION]... [FILE]...
     
AVAILABLE OPTIONS:
    --file [FILE]       -- write contents of a file

EXAMPLES
    write-to-history "echo 'hello'"
    write-to-history --file /path/to/file.txt